A6. COMBINED NAME COLUMN — Auto-split detection

In src/lib/parsers/column-mapper.ts, add 
detection and auto-splitting for single 
combined name columns.

Context: CSVs from event organizers frequently 
use a single "Name", "Full Name", or "Attendee 
Name" column instead of separate First/Last 
columns. Currently these produce blank 
firstName and lastName and the contact goes 
to unresolved confidence.

Step 1 — Detection:
Add these aliases to CONTACT_HEADER_MAP 
mapping to a new sentinel value "fullName":
- name
- fullname
- attendeename
- participantname
- attendee
- contactname

Step 2 — Splitting in mapContactRow:
After building the row, if row.fullName is set 
and both firstName and lastName are empty:

a. If value contains a comma → treat as 
   "Last, First" format. Split on comma, 
   trim both parts, assign: 
   firstName = second part, lastName = first part

b. Otherwise → split on first whitespace.
   First token → firstName
   Remaining tokens joined → lastName

c. If only one token (no space, no comma) → 
   assign to firstName, leave lastName empty

d. Strip leading honorifics before splitting:
   Dr., Mr., Mrs., Ms., Prof., Sr., Jr.
   (case-insensitive, with or without period)

Step 3 — Cleanup:
Do not store "fullName" on the row object 
after splitting. It is a parsing-only sentinel 
and should not appear in the enriched row data.

Step 4 — Docs update:
In docs/TECHNICAL_ARCHITECTURE.md, add a note 
in the relevant section that combined name 
columns are now detected and auto-split during 
parsing.

